1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,877
[AREZA]<i> I know what kind</i>
<i>of bombs they planted.</i>

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:04,796
<i>Military-type IED.</i>

3
00:00:04,879 --> 00:00:07,215
<i>Lieutenant, the bomb here is rigged.</i>

4
00:00:07,298 --> 00:00:08,967
<i>We can't move it. It might explode.</i>

5
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:10,260
<i>Do you know how to disarm bombs?</i>

6
00:00:10,343 --> 00:00:12,637
<i>I'll teach you how to disarm a bomb.</i>

7
00:00:12,721 --> 00:00:15,181
<i>Find the latch</i>
<i>at the side of the doorframe.</i>

8
00:00:15,265 --> 00:00:16,099
<i>Open it.</i>

9
00:00:16,182 --> 00:00:17,559
<i>Liam, what do you see?</i>

10
00:00:17,642 --> 00:00:19,269
[LIAM] <i>There's a small control board</i>

11
00:00:19,352 --> 00:00:21,604
<i>and a terminal block</i>
<i>numbered one to three.</i>

12
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:24,065
[AREZA] <i>It only passes through</i>
<i>terminal number three.</i>

13
00:00:24,149 --> 00:00:27,318
<i>The rest are decoys or secondary lines.</i>

14
00:00:27,402 --> 00:00:29,237
<i>Don't touch lines one and two.</i>

15
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:31,197
<i>They're not part of the active circuit.</i>

16
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:33,283
<i>Good job, Liam.</i>
<i>The bomb has been disarmed.</i>

17
00:00:33,366 --> 00:00:34,659
<i>Yes!</i>

18
00:00:34,743 --> 00:00:36,995
<i>- Let's go!</i>
<i>- Come on!</i>

19
00:00:37,078 --> 00:00:40,040
- [PHONE RINGING]
<i>- Lucas, pick up. They're here.</i>

20
00:00:40,999 --> 00:00:41,916
[AREZA] Yes?

21
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,377
<i>Emil Padua's daughter is in the ward.</i>

22
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:46,713
<i>Most of them are on the rooftop.</i>

23
00:00:46,796 --> 00:00:48,548
<i>Okay. We'll handle them.</i>

24
00:00:48,631 --> 00:00:51,342
<i>Sir, extracting the hostages</i>
<i>won't be easy.</i>

25
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:53,511
<i>There are bombs attached to them.</i>

26
00:00:53,595 --> 00:00:55,764
<i>They used a transmitter</i>
<i>and receiver module.</i>

27
00:00:55,847 --> 00:00:59,434
<i>After we secure the hostages, that's when</i>
<i>we're going to remove the bombs.</i>

28
00:00:59,517 --> 00:01:00,685
[LIAM] <i>We need to move fast.</i>

29
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:02,771
<i>Before the sedated guys</i>
<i>regain consciousness.</i>

30
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:06,858
<i>What did you do?</i>

31
00:01:06,941 --> 00:01:08,735
[MACKY] <i>I broke the transmitter.</i>

32
00:01:08,818 --> 00:01:10,403
<i>The bombs won't explode.</i>

33
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:13,490
<i>They use the transmitter</i>
<i>to trigger the bomb,</i>

34
00:01:13,573 --> 00:01:15,408
<i>using distance as a trigger.</i>

35
00:01:15,492 --> 00:01:17,535
<i>Now that the transmitter is broken,</i>

36
00:01:17,619 --> 00:01:19,329
<i>the bombs are useless.</i>

37
00:01:20,288 --> 00:01:21,873
<i>Good job.</i>

38
00:01:21,956 --> 00:01:23,792
<i>Is he really my father?</i>

39
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:26,586
<i>Yes.</i>

40
00:01:26,669 --> 00:01:29,798
<i>You already saw what kind of person he is.</i>

41
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:32,383
<i>Do you still want to recognize him</i>
<i>as your father?</i>

42
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:37,305
Olsen.

43
00:01:39,182 --> 00:01:40,391
How are you?

44
00:01:41,976 --> 00:01:43,311
I'm still not okay.

45
00:01:43,394 --> 00:01:44,729
[SNIFFLES]

46
00:01:45,313 --> 00:01:47,273
There are so many things on my mind.

47
00:01:47,357 --> 00:01:50,026
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

48
00:01:50,777 --> 00:01:52,237
What is it?

49
00:01:53,655 --> 00:01:56,366
Macky broke the bomb transmitter.

50
00:01:57,784 --> 00:01:59,410
It's been deactivated.

51
00:02:00,245 --> 00:02:01,871
It won't explode anymore.

52
00:02:04,249 --> 00:02:05,416
What are you up to?

53
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:08,628
I'm a nurse.

54
00:02:09,546 --> 00:02:11,297
I was just checking his wounds.

55
00:02:12,423 --> 00:02:13,716
Make it quick.

56
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:15,677
Go back there right away.

57
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:20,807
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

58
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:22,392
Macky has a plan.

59
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:26,354
We'll attack them together.

60
00:02:27,355 --> 00:02:28,982
We just need to wait for the right moment.

61
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:31,234
Ice.

62
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:34,571
We don't stand a chance against them.

63
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:39,701
We need to get the guns

64
00:02:40,493 --> 00:02:42,078
that we took from the resort.

65
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:46,541
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:02:46,624 --> 00:02:48,376
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

67
00:02:48,459 --> 00:02:51,880
Tell Macky and Fin

68
00:02:53,631 --> 00:02:55,049
that I also have a plan.

69
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,552
What's your plan?

70
00:02:57,635 --> 00:03:03,892
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

71
00:03:12,191 --> 00:03:19,032
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

72
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:56,736
[LUCAS SIGHS]

73
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:01,074
Brother.

74
00:04:02,575 --> 00:04:05,745
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have
mentioned Junior.

75
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:12,669
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

76
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:14,629
He was only three years old then.

77
00:04:15,838 --> 00:04:17,674
I promised him I'd take him out.

78
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:23,012
But I couldn't stop myself from drinking
before picking him up at his mom's.

79
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:27,058
You didn't mean for it to happen.

80
00:04:28,643 --> 00:04:29,894
You're right, Lucas.

81
00:04:29,978 --> 00:04:34,023
What kind of father would want to be
the cause of his own child's death?

82
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:37,610
[CLEARS THROAT]

83
00:04:42,073 --> 00:04:43,741
Can we talk?

84
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:50,456
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

85
00:04:58,047 --> 00:04:59,465
We're on the first floor.

86
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:00,883
We're on the way to the commissary.

87
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,260
The plan is simple.

88
00:05:02,343 --> 00:05:06,389
Surprise Padua and his men
and secure the hostages.

89
00:05:07,765 --> 00:05:10,351
[CABRAL ON THE PHONE]
<i>Copy, Areza. Backup's ready.</i>

90
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:12,020
They'll just wait for your signal.

91
00:05:12,103 --> 00:05:15,648
Just make sure that the hostage-takers
don't find out what you're doing.

92
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:20,361
Otherwise, they might do to the hostages
what they did to Jacinto.

93
00:05:20,445 --> 00:05:22,572
- Yes, sir. Let's move.
- Let's go.

94
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:27,035
My mother told me…

95
00:05:29,871 --> 00:05:34,208
that my real father died
before I was born.

96
00:05:34,292 --> 00:05:37,462
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

97
00:05:37,545 --> 00:05:38,963
I only found out now

98
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,258
that she lied to me.

99
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:48,431
My real father is still alive, and…

100
00:05:51,893 --> 00:05:53,311
I really feel…

101
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:57,273
that it's you.

102
00:05:57,356 --> 00:06:03,404
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

103
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:08,701
If you're really my son,
what do you want to happen?

104
00:06:12,413 --> 00:06:17,168
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

105
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:21,923
What is Olsen doing?

106
00:06:22,006 --> 00:06:24,717
Apparently, the bombs are useless now.

107
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:28,262
Macky disabled the transmitter.

108
00:06:28,846 --> 00:06:30,556
We can escape.

109
00:06:31,682 --> 00:06:34,227
Olsen will try to get a gun.

110
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:35,686
Gun?

111
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:38,064
What are you talking about?

112
00:06:38,147 --> 00:06:41,818
Olsen said we should stay alert.

113
00:06:42,819 --> 00:06:44,153
Are you crazy?

114
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:46,697
Why aren't you stopping your son?

115
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:48,825
He's going to get all of us in trouble.

116
00:06:48,908 --> 00:06:50,076
Including Liam.

117
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:53,204
Olsen's right.

118
00:06:55,289 --> 00:06:57,041
This may be our last chance.

119
00:06:57,834 --> 00:07:00,128
We have to fight.

120
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:02,004
You're taking their side again?

121
00:07:02,088 --> 00:07:03,714
I'm not taking any sides.

122
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:06,259
Not Olsen's. Not Wendy's.

123
00:07:07,468 --> 00:07:10,680
My only goal here
is for all of us to escape safely.

124
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:13,099
We all know that they are
going to kill us,

125
00:07:13,182 --> 00:07:15,518
so we need to fight back.

126
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:21,023
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

127
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:22,817
Let Mama go.

128
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:25,069
[SCOFFS]

129
00:07:28,197 --> 00:07:29,824
Are you an idiot?

130
00:07:31,576 --> 00:07:33,995
Do you know what your mother did to me?

131
00:07:34,579 --> 00:07:35,496
Hmm?

132
00:07:36,581 --> 00:07:38,749
She just used me.

133
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,961
If I'd really gotten her pregnant
and I'd found out,

134
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:44,547
I would've taken responsibility.

135
00:07:45,173 --> 00:07:47,341
But what did she do
when there was a problem?

136
00:07:47,925 --> 00:07:51,179
She disappeared without a word.

137
00:07:52,513 --> 00:07:54,849
She made fools out of both of us.

138
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:58,936
We're the same.

139
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,230
I just said I didn't know, right?

140
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:04,817
That's why I'm asking you myself.

141
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:08,946
As…

142
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:12,158
As your son.

143
00:08:12,241 --> 00:08:15,286
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:08:15,369 --> 00:08:16,370
Pa…

145
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:19,373
Please.

146
00:08:24,253 --> 00:08:25,338
[CHUCKLES]

147
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:31,177
I'm not even sure if you're really my son.

148
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:35,389
But one thing I'm sure of is that
you're your mother's son!

149
00:08:37,099 --> 00:08:40,728
And like her, you're probably

150
00:08:41,395 --> 00:08:45,066
just taking me for a ride!

151
00:08:45,149 --> 00:08:50,571
You know, I never imagined
I'd meet my father like this.

152
00:08:54,158 --> 00:08:56,410
But what can I do? You're here.

153
00:08:56,494 --> 00:08:59,413
We're here now. What else can we do?

154
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:03,501
So…

155
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:07,588
why don't we start over?

156
00:09:08,297 --> 00:09:14,512
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

157
00:09:17,431 --> 00:09:23,646
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:09:23,729 --> 00:09:25,189
[MACKY] I can't stand this anymore.

159
00:09:26,315 --> 00:09:28,901
I've had enough! I'm sick of this!

160
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:30,111
Wait, wait, wait!

161
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:32,572
Are you out of your mind?!

162
00:09:32,655 --> 00:09:35,116
If you leave, you're going to explode!
You're going to die!

163
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:36,534
Let me go!

164
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:40,162
- [FIN] Fine! Go! I won't stop you!
- I'm really leaving.

165
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:41,914
All you do is cause trouble anyway!

166
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:44,000
- For your dad and for all of us!
- [ICE] Fin, stop.

167
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:49,171
- Good riddance! Go die for all we care!
- What did you say?!

168
00:09:49,255 --> 00:09:51,215
- [LUCAS] Hey!
- [SENATOR MARISTELLA] Macky!

169
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:55,595
Oh really?! What, think we'll do nothing
just because you've got a bandage?!

170
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:56,512
Shut up!

171
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:58,347
Why? Just because you're
the senator's son?!

172
00:09:58,431 --> 00:10:01,309
If you want to die, do it alone!

173
00:10:01,392 --> 00:10:04,562
- You really won't stop?!
- [ICE] Please don't hurt him!

174
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:07,064
- [WHIMPERING] Please…
- Sir…

175
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:08,149
[KEYPAD BEEPING]

176
00:10:08,816 --> 00:10:11,736
[LINE RINGING]

177
00:10:11,819 --> 00:10:14,905
Lucas, please pick up. Come on.

178
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:17,867
[CALL DISCONNECTING]

179
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:20,328
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

180
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:21,912
- Please stop…
- Sir…

181
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:24,081
[FIN] Sir, I don't want to die.

182
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:25,583
I don't want to die--

183
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:26,917
[GRUNTS]

184
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:30,046
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

185
00:10:30,129 --> 00:10:31,839
[HOMER] Shut up, all of you!

186
00:10:31,922 --> 00:10:33,049
[MACKY] Let go of me!

187
00:10:35,176 --> 00:10:37,345
[FIN] Why are you beating me up
instead of him?!

188
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:39,221
- Beat him up!
- Is that what you want?

189
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:41,140
- [ICE] Stop it.
- Is that what you want?!

190
00:10:41,223 --> 00:10:43,059
Is that what you want?!

191
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:44,977
Get him over here.

192
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:46,937
Why?

193
00:10:47,438 --> 00:10:49,023
[GRUNTS]

194
00:10:50,149 --> 00:10:51,484
- [BLOWS LANDING]
- [MACKY GRUNTS]

195
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:52,693
Hey, that's enough!

196
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:54,195
Hey!

197
00:10:54,278 --> 00:10:55,237
[MACKY INHALES SHARPLY]

198
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:57,281
[OLSEN] That's enough.

199
00:10:57,365 --> 00:10:59,867
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

200
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:03,162
[LINE RINGS, THEN DISCONNECTS]

201
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:06,207
[MACKY BREATHES HEAVILY, GROANS]

202
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:07,541
Stop it.

203
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:09,335
[MACKY GRUNTS]

204
00:11:09,418 --> 00:11:11,170
Get back to your places!

205
00:11:11,253 --> 00:11:13,130
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

206
00:11:13,214 --> 00:11:14,131
Fin.

207
00:11:23,265 --> 00:11:24,141
[HOMER] Hurry!

208
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:29,271
[MACKY BREATHING HEAVILY]

209
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:30,773
[HOMER] Settle down now.

210
00:11:37,822 --> 00:11:44,453
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

211
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:49,750
We're almost there.

212
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,795
[EMIL ON RADIO] <i>Dado, come in.</i>

213
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:54,964
<i>Dado?</i>

214
00:11:55,798 --> 00:11:57,007
It's Emil Padua.

215
00:11:58,843 --> 00:12:01,137
We need to secure Dado
before Emil finds out.

216
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:02,972
- Let's go.
- Let's move!

217
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:22,616
Captain Jericho Jacinto?

218
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:26,745
Sir?

219
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:29,957
Are you ready to talk?

220
00:12:32,042 --> 00:12:35,504
Many lives depend on
the information you'll tell me.

221
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:41,677
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:12:43,095 --> 00:12:44,305
[EMIL] Dado?

223
00:12:44,388 --> 00:12:45,264
[RADIO STATIC]

224
00:12:45,347 --> 00:12:49,101
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:54,356
Dado's not answering.

226
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:56,358
What happened to him?

227
00:12:56,442 --> 00:13:00,738
He went with Liam Roja
so he could lead him to his companions.

228
00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:05,075
They must've encountered
a problem because of Liam Roja.

229
00:13:07,912 --> 00:13:10,998
He won't stop until he saves everyone.

230
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:18,881
Well, the opposite will happen.

231
00:13:20,424 --> 00:13:22,051
Because of him,

232
00:13:23,511 --> 00:13:25,179
they will all die.

233
00:13:25,262 --> 00:13:32,228
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:35,856
[GUN COCKS]

235
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:51,872
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

236
00:14:00,923 --> 00:14:03,050
Dado and his companion are gone.

237
00:14:03,133 --> 00:14:04,802
He might have told Emil!

238
00:14:04,885 --> 00:14:07,680
They might kill more hostages
if you attack them.

239
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:12,142
All units, hold position!

240
00:14:12,226 --> 00:14:13,978
I repeat, hold position!

241
00:14:14,061 --> 00:14:16,981
Lieutenant, I have to go back upstairs.

242
00:14:17,064 --> 00:14:19,191
The lives of my mom
and the hostages are in danger.

243
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:22,319
I'm going to talk to Emil Padua.

244
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,572
Stay here!

245
00:14:24,655 --> 00:14:28,868
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

246
00:14:29,618 --> 00:14:30,786
[MUSIC FADES]

247
00:14:32,454 --> 00:14:36,750
Lieutenant Areza was the one
who had evidence gathered against you.

248
00:14:39,295 --> 00:14:41,463
You have a connection with Emil Padua.

249
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:45,593
You were in the same unit together.

250
00:14:47,511 --> 00:14:54,435
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

251
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:00,983
And his release from jail…

252
00:15:02,443 --> 00:15:04,403
You were the one who arranged it, right?

253
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:11,410
So you can't deny Liam
and Greta Roja's accusations against you.

254
00:15:11,493 --> 00:15:13,954
That you are involved in what's happening.

255
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:16,415
If you want to know everything…

256
00:15:18,042 --> 00:15:19,668
the truth…

257
00:15:22,254 --> 00:15:24,131
I'll tell you, sir.

258
00:15:24,214 --> 00:15:25,549
Everything.

259
00:15:27,259 --> 00:15:28,344
But…

260
00:15:30,179 --> 00:15:32,097
you have to promise me

261
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:37,478
you'll protect me
once all of this comes out.

262
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:41,649
And what kind of deal
are you asking for, Jacinto?

263
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:43,859
Immunity.

264
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:48,280
And protection for my family.

265
00:15:48,364 --> 00:15:51,951
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

266
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:55,037
- Liam!
- We don't have time!

267
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:57,164
They'll kill my parents
and the other hostages!

268
00:15:57,247 --> 00:16:02,544
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

269
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:04,338
I can't let you attack them like this.

270
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:07,967
If something happens to them,
it'll be my fault!

271
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,011
[GRUNTS, PANTS]

272
00:16:11,095 --> 00:16:13,389
We will negotiate with them.

273
00:16:13,472 --> 00:16:15,724
They haven't gotten what they want.

274
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:18,644
We can't negotiate with demons!

275
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:20,896
What's your plan, huh?

276
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:22,189
A surprise attack?

277
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:23,983
They've probably already thought of that!

278
00:16:24,692 --> 00:16:25,734
Liam!

279
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:28,320
Listen to me.

280
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:31,073
They might've already gotten the money,

281
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:33,826
but they don't know
how they'll get out of here.

282
00:16:34,743 --> 00:16:36,954
And we'll use that to negotiate.

283
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:43,836
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:48,632
You're asking for a lot, Jacinto.

285
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:52,136
Especially for someone
who has lied over and over again.

286
00:16:53,595 --> 00:16:55,597
But fine. I'll indulge you.

287
00:16:56,640 --> 00:17:00,060
That is, if you give me new
and useful information.

288
00:17:01,645 --> 00:17:03,355
But if it's just garbage,

289
00:17:04,356 --> 00:17:07,109
then… no deal.

290
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:10,654
I'm not the mastermind

291
00:17:11,488 --> 00:17:14,199
of the hostage taking at La Playa Roja.

292
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:17,369
[SCOFFS] Then who is?

293
00:17:17,453 --> 00:17:19,371
Emil Padua?

294
00:17:19,455 --> 00:17:21,832
[CHUCKLES]

295
00:17:21,915 --> 00:17:24,293
That's useless information.

296
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:27,713
You know,
you're all going to rot in prison.

297
00:17:27,796 --> 00:17:29,506
It's not Emil Padua.

298
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:34,386
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

299
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:35,512
It's Roja.

300
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:37,723
What?

301
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:43,937
Greta Roja is the real mastermind

302
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:46,774
of the hostage taking at La Playa Roja.

303
00:17:46,857 --> 00:17:51,904
[UNSETTLING MUSIC SWELLS]

304
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:55,824
She told me

305
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:58,827
to recruit people

306
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:01,914
to carry out the hostage taking.

307
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:06,001
So I approached Emil Padua

308
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:10,130
and told him to lead
and put together the team

309
00:18:10,881 --> 00:18:12,966
that would carry out the operation.

310
00:18:14,551 --> 00:18:18,388
And why would Greta Roja have
her own resort taken hostage?

311
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:20,224
For money.

312
00:18:22,476 --> 00:18:24,311
That's it, sir.

313
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:30,818
Mrs. Roja lost
hundreds of millions gambling.

314
00:18:31,401 --> 00:18:34,279
To recover that money,

315
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:36,156
she made sure…

316
00:18:38,826 --> 00:18:44,206
she'd get a big cut
from the hostage taking.

317
00:18:49,044 --> 00:18:50,712
[GRETA] <i>Captain Jacinto.</i>

318
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:53,173
<i>Please, just call me Jericho.</i>

319
00:18:54,049 --> 00:18:57,302
<i>I asked you to meet with me</i>
<i>to make a proposal.</i>

320
00:18:57,386 --> 00:19:01,056
<i>So I can at least start</i>
<i>paying off my debt to you.</i>

321
00:19:01,765 --> 00:19:04,601
<i>Everything, including the interest.</i>

322
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:10,357
<i>You know I own a luxury resort, right?</i>

323
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:11,650
[CHUCKLES]

324
00:19:11,733 --> 00:19:13,527
<i>You're going to use it as collateral?</i>

325
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:16,822
Something like that.

326
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:22,536
I'll use my VIP guests as collateral.

327
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:24,621
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

328
00:19:24,705 --> 00:19:26,081
How?

329
00:19:26,874 --> 00:19:30,836
<i>Even though the security</i>
<i>of La Playa Roja is tight,</i>

330
00:19:30,919 --> 00:19:34,798
<i>theft can still happen.</i>

331
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:40,220
<i>The VIP guests who check in…</i>

332
00:19:40,304 --> 00:19:42,514
<i>their jewelry is no joke.</i>

333
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:44,808
[CHUCKLES]

334
00:19:44,892 --> 00:19:46,351
<i>So to pay off your debt,</i>

335
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:51,148
<i>you want me to conspire with you</i>
<i>to rob your own guests?</i>

336
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:55,319
<i>So you also think like a criminal.</i>

337
00:19:55,903 --> 00:19:58,447
<i>I just don't know what to do anymore.</i>

338
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:00,741
<i>I'm in a tight spot.</i>

339
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:04,286
<i>My husband doesn't know</i>

340
00:20:04,369 --> 00:20:06,747
<i>that we barely have</i>
<i>any money left in the bank.</i>

341
00:20:07,372 --> 00:20:09,541
<i>You think like a criminal, but…</i>

342
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:12,669
<i>You know what?</i>

343
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:15,839
<i>If you're planning</i>
<i>to commit a crime anyway,</i>

344
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:18,675
<i>go big.</i>

345
00:20:20,510 --> 00:20:21,803
<i>W-What do you mean?</i>

346
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:26,308
<i>How much would we</i>
<i>even get from a simple robbery?</i>

347
00:20:27,976 --> 00:20:29,269
<i>Why not…</i>

348
00:20:31,063 --> 00:20:32,481
<i>do a hostage taking instead?</i>

349
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:38,946
<i>When does your resort have</i>
<i>a lot of VIP guests booked?</i>

350
00:20:39,947 --> 00:20:41,531
<i>We'll do it that day.</i>

351
00:20:42,282 --> 00:20:45,911
<i>I'll put together a group</i>
<i>to attack your island.</i>

352
00:20:45,994 --> 00:20:47,371
<i>What if…</i>

353
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:48,872
<i>What if someone gets hurt?</i>

354
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:51,792
<i>We're just going to scare them.</i>

355
00:20:54,169 --> 00:20:55,212
<i>Are you sure?</i>

356
00:20:55,295 --> 00:20:57,214
<i>To make it more convincing,</i>

357
00:20:58,548 --> 00:21:02,052
<i>your family</i>
<i>will have to be held hostage too.</i>

358
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:04,721
But…

359
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:07,891
she strictly instructed me

360
00:21:09,393 --> 00:21:14,147
not to let anyone else know
that she was behind it.

361
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:17,484
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

362
00:21:17,567 --> 00:21:19,403
Believe me, sir.

363
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:24,950
I can prove everything I said.

364
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:30,205
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

365
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:34,334
[DADO PANTING]

366
00:21:34,418 --> 00:21:40,257
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:21:41,341 --> 00:21:42,592
Boss.

368
00:21:42,676 --> 00:21:44,052
What happened to you?

369
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:45,971
[DADO PANTING]

370
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:47,347
Liam escaped.

371
00:21:49,391 --> 00:21:51,643
He took my gun and radio.

372
00:21:51,727 --> 00:21:54,438
And Conrad… He's dead.

373
00:21:54,521 --> 00:22:00,527
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

374
00:22:00,610 --> 00:22:02,904
We'll teach Liam Roja a lesson.

375
00:22:03,947 --> 00:22:05,824
We'll kill his mother.

376
00:22:06,408 --> 00:22:07,993
- Yes, sir.
- Let's go.

377
00:22:08,744 --> 00:22:15,709
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

378
00:22:28,555 --> 00:22:30,807
<i>Any mistake could put</i>
<i>the hostages at risk.</i>

379
00:22:30,891 --> 00:22:33,977
<i>I will make your son pay</i>
<i>for what he did to me.</i>

380
00:22:35,812 --> 00:22:36,855
- [GUNSHOT]
<i>- Ma!</i>

381
00:22:36,938 --> 00:22:38,482
<i>We need backup on the rooftop.</i>

382
00:22:39,816 --> 00:22:42,069
- [MACKY] <i>Hurry!</i>
<i>- Nobody move!</i>

383
00:22:42,152 --> 00:22:48,033
[RAPID GUNSHOTS]

384
00:22:48,116 --> 00:22:48,992
[SHOUTS]

385
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:53,830
<i>Homer, don't let your son get away!</i>

386
00:22:53,914 --> 00:23:00,003
[RAPID GUNSHOTS]

387
00:23:00,087 --> 00:23:06,384
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
